Nollywood rising star Vicky Nwogu has opined that the life of an actor is a series of experiences. In a recent chat with The Nation, Vicky revealed that she’s happy with her growth as a rising act in Nollywood.   Oxlade a stalker, says unidentified lady in s3x tape     Yekeen Adewale exposes kidnappers’ strength in ‘Asiri…     Basketmouth sets to release ‘Horoscope’   “I believe that movement in the right direction however slow, is progress nonetheless. I am happy with the knowledge, the projects, and the experiences so far. Thankfully the life of an actor is a series of experiences. I’m open to learning, unlearning, and re-learn,” she said. Continuing, Nwogu said, “I have also come to understand that focus is key. I always say that the mind is like a muscle, the more you train it, the stronger it becomes. My goal is to have a variety of experiences.”